<div><div><h4>Job Description</h4></div><div><div><span><div><div><strong>CHEMIST</strong></div><div><strong>Terengganu / Negeri Sembilan / Johor/ Pahang</strong></div><div><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></div><ul><li>Implement, monitor and take action in laboratory operation in accordance with the rules and objectives of the company.</li><li>Responsible to assist Head Analysis Lab in the operation and administrative of the Lab in accordance with the rules and objectives of the company.</li><li>Implement and taking action to optimize lab efficiency and sample analysis effectively.</li><li>Troubleshoot and to do improvement &amp; corrective action on lab operation and technical issue.</li><li>Responsible for the laboratory activities such as analysis operation (effluent and palm), maintenance, crosscheck, R&amp;D, ISO, audit, training, and etc.</li><li>Responsible for lab process control and quality of the product (analysis results) within control limit.</li><li>Issue certificate of analysis (COA) within deadline</li><li>Responsible for the safety of employees, machineries and others including of samples, certificate of analysis, spare parts and properties of the lab.</li><li>Participate in Proficiency Testing by Jabatan Kimia Malaysia (JKM) and achieve a good z-score marks.</li><li>Responsible as Approved Signatory to sign a laboratory test reports or all other documents as required by law or the Department of Standards Malaysia.</li><li>Responsible for management of ISO IEC 17025:2017.</li><li>Responsible to plan training &amp; competency programme and train the staffs.</li><li>Responsible to maintain a good communication with the lab customers</li></ul><div><strong>Requirements</strong></div><ul><li>Degree in Chemistry or its equivalent</li><li>Registered Chemist with Malaysian Institute Of Chemistry (IKM) is an added advantage</li><li>Minimum 2 years related working experience</li></ul></div></span></div></div></div>
